“Be so confident in God’s plan that you don’t get upset when things go your way” 
I read this quote the other day and it stuck to me. I kept thinking about it. God am I reflecting this kind of confidence in your plan? I’ve cried and I’ve gotten upset…am I doubting you? But I think I was missing the point. It’s ok to weep and to work through the heartbreak when what you thought was God’s plan isn’t. You had this vision of what it would look like. But even through those tears and disappointment, faith is saying I know you closed this door for a reason and better is coming. “Thank you Lord.” Faith is a heart of gratitude through all seasons. This may have been what I thought was best for my life but God I want YOUR best. Thank you for your protection from what is not from you. Faith is trust that the “No” and “not yet” are still God’s best. 

“Consider it pure joy, my brothers and sisters, whenever you face trials of many kinds, because you know that the testing of your faith produces perseverance. Let perseverance finish its work so that you may be mature and complete, not lacking anything.” James 1:2-4

SLEEK & VOLUMINOUS ponytail tutorial for your next dirty hair day 😝 
Start with smoothing creme and run through your roots. Tie hair off with a ponytail diving the tail into two sections. Loop the last bit of the ponytail holder through the top section to add lift to the tail.

If you want to grow out your brows for that thick fluffy brow looks here is what I did! Cause trust me I did nottt start with thick brows! Actually I had hardly any brow hair growing up. It’s a process (and not a pretty one) to grow them out but so worth it! 
1. Don’t touch your brows with tweezers or wax. I know it’s not ideal but you are trying to grow them out so you need to let them grow! Promise you will thank yourself later!
2. Brow serum! I have used multiple in my life and my top two are @grandecosmetics and @revitalashcosmetics 
3. To make them look even ticker, color them with “just for men.” Sounds weird I know but this will make your brows look TWICE as thick
